B-Tree index

Composite index 
- an index on two or more columns of a table. Unlike single-column indices, the order of columns in a composite index is crucial for its effectiveness.
- если индексация по age-status, запрос надо посылать с такой же очередностью, иначе индекс работать не будет
- но можно послать запрос с одной частью индекса без другой (age bez statusa)

Covered index
- includes all the columns needed to answer a specific query, so we can retrieve the required data directly from the index 
without having to access the underlying table.
When a query is executed, the database optimizer checks if there's an index that covers all the columns referenced in the SELECT, WHERE, JOIN, or ORDER BY clauses.
If such an index exists (a covering index), the database can fetch the data solely from the index, 
which is typically faster because indexes are smaller and more optimized for read operations than full tables.

